{"questionId":"9067255","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Phosphatidylcholine is an example of a phospholipid found in lecithin.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Phosphatidylcholine may be formed from propane-1,2,3-triol, two lauric acid molecules, phosphoric acid and the choline cation.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3ceda054831af77090fe92b52e6cdd8bb12f3f85.png\" width=\"698\" height=\"97\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Identify the type of reaction in (a).</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">condensation <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note</strong>: Accept “esterification”.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Accept “nucleophilic substitution/S<sub>N</sub>”.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067255","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ2.a(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Identify the type of reaction in (a).","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","B: Biochemistry","B.1 Introduction to biochemistry","Options","B: Biochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}